<module>
    <h>balla</h>
    <p><g>balla</g>
        <en>a wall</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
            noun</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section>
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p>Examples of <g>balla</g> with the <a href="?xx=nouns/definite_article">definite
                    article</a> as pre-specifier – <ul>
                    <li>nominative – <g>am balla</g>
                        <en>the wall</en> – <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Tha am balla àrd.</gd>
                                <tr>The wall is high.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                    <li>dative – <g>(air) a’ bhalla</g>
                        <en>(on) the wall</en> – <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>An robh an clachair ag obair air a’ bhalla fad an latha an dé?
                                    Bha.</gd>
                                <tr>Was the mason working on the wall all day yesterday? Yes, he
                                    was.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section>
            <h>subject</h>
            <p>Examples of <g>balla</g> as the subject of the predicative verb <a href="?gd=bi"
                        ><g>bi</g></a>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha robh am balla àrd.</gd>
                        <tr>The wall wasn’t high.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h>complement</h>
            <module>
                <h>air balla / air a’ bhalla</h>
                <p>Examples of <g>balla</g> as the complement of the preposition <a href="?gd=air"
                            ><g>air</g></a>
                    <en>on</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Bha an clachair ag obair air a’ bhalla fad an latha.</gd>
                            <tr>The mason working on the wall all day.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 20 [adapted]</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl>
                </p>
            </module>
        </section>
    </section>

</module>
